Ghosts of Git
How i imporve my workflow with bash aliases for common git commands

gis
Shows git status.
git status

glop
Shows git log with p Parameter, to list file changes
git log -p

glog
just the normal git log
git log

gline
Shows one line log of commits
git log --oneline

glob 
Shows a prettyfied version of the git log
git log --graph --pretty=format:'%Cred%h%Creset-%C(yellow)%d%Creset %s %Cgreen(%cr) %C(bold blue)<%an>%Creset' --abbrev-commit
--date=relative

glast
shows the last commit
git log -1 HEAD --stat

gmit <MESSAGE>
Commits Files with a message
git commit -m "Some Message"

gadda
Adds all Changes to Stage
git add .

gadd <FILENAMES>
Adds <FILENAMES> to Stage
git add <FILENAMES>

gush
Push stuff 
git push

gout <BRANCHNAME>
git checkout <BRANCHNAME>


granches
list all branches in a prettyfied manner sorted by committerdate

gmerge
git merge

greate <BRANCHNAME>
git checkout -b <BRANCHNAME>

gash and gasha
git stash and git stash apply

gonf
git config --global -l






 
